# Time & attendance phases (production track)

Work in order: **Phase 0** (policy words) → **1** punch truth → **2** breaks → **3** timesheet packet (optional) → **4** OT rules → **5** PTO + ledger → **6** notifications → **7** payroll export (CSV).  
Stay in **hours + export**, not tax/withholding.

## After completing each phase

Run a **quick QA pass** before merging or tagging:

1. **Smoke:** happy path + one failure path (permission denied, validation error).
2. **Data:** confirm Supabase rows / columns match the feature (or RPC returns expected shape).
3. **RBAC:** with `RBAC_ENABLED=true`, confirm viewers without permission cannot perform manager actions.
4. **Regression:** touch the previous phase’s critical path (e.g. after Phase 2, still clock in/out and see punches).

Document anything that is **deferred** (e.g. “OT deferred to payroll”) so scope stays honest.

## Phase 1 QA checklist (punch truth)

- [ ] Self-serve **Clock in** creates `time_entries` with `punch_source` (`web` or `mobile`) and optional `job_code`.
- [ ] **Clock out** closes the open row; optional GPS on clock-out when geofence enabled.
- [ ] **client_request_id** / double-submit: second identical request does not duplicate (idempotency).
- [ ] **Geofence:** when location has lat/lng/radius, clock-in without GPS fails; with position inside radius succeeds.
- [ ] Manager **Adjust times** saves `edited_at` / `edit_reason`, clears `approved_at`, and appears on **Security audit** (time clock manage permission).
- [ ] Times refresh in UI after punch / adjust (`router.refresh`).

## Phase 2 QA checklist (breaks as data)

- [ ] **Start break** (unpaid or paid) creates `time_entry_breaks` with `ended_at` null; only one open break per punch.
- [ ] **End break** sets `ended_at`; **Clock out** also closes any open break with the same timestamp as clock-out.
- [ ] Punch table **Breaks** column shows a short summary (unpaid / paid minutes, or “On break” when in progress).
- [ ] Phase 1 still works: clock in/out, adjust times, geofence path unchanged.

## Phase 3 QA checklist (timesheet packet)

- [ ] **Timesheets** tab shows punches for the selected period (existing grid).
- [ ] **Export CSV** downloads rows matching the current period + filters (search/status) with columns: employee, times, breaks summary, status, job code, punch source.
- [ ] Phase 1–2 paths still work after export (read-only client download).

## Phase 4–7 (status)

- **4 — OT rules:** not implemented — blocked until org defines thresholds (weekly/daily, flags on punches or summary).
- **5 — PTO + ledger:** **partial** — `time_off_records` + manager log + **employee request (pending) + manager approve/deny** + surfacing in UI; **accrual ledger / balances** still TODO.
- **6 — Notifications:** in-app/email for late punch / OT / approvals (TBD).
- **7 — Payroll export:** CSV from Phase 3; extend with provider-specific columns / pay period close if needed.
